## Step 3 â€” Post-Task Memory Update

After completing any significant task (code generation, spec creation, plan
finalization, checklist run):

1. Update `memory-bank/activeContext.md` with:
   - What was just done (1-2 sentences)
   - Which files were created or modified
   - What the next logical step is

2. Update `memory-bank/progress.md` if:
   - A task moved from Not Started â†’ In Progress
   - A task moved from In Progress â†’ Done
   - A new blocker was discovered

3. **Staleness check:** If any memory-bank file has a `Last Updated` date older
   than 7 days, output a warning:
   > âš  `memory-bank/[filename].md` was last updated [N] days ago. Run
   > `/context-sync` or manually update it before this session's changes
   > become invisible to future sessions.

