## Violations

### âťŚ Violation 1 â€” Generating code without reading memory-bank

**Trigger:** User asks: *"Add a caching layer to the product query."*

**Bad behavior:**
> Agent immediately writes a handler using `IMemoryCache` â€” which the project
> already phased out in favor of Redis + FusionCache two sprints ago.
> Conflict discovered only in code review.

**Correct behavior:**
> Agent reads `memory-bank/techContext.md`, sees `FusionCache 0.19` listed
> under caching stack, then reads `memory-bank/systemPatterns.md` and finds
> the established `ICacheService` interface. Agent generates the caching
> layer using `IFusionCache` and the existing pattern â€” no conflict.

---

### âťŚ Violation 2 â€” Starting a feature already In Progress

**Trigger:** User asks: *"Start implementing the notifications feature."*

**Bad behavior:**
> Agent jumps straight to `/speckit-git-feature notifications` without
> checking progress.md â€” creates a duplicate branch when `feature/notifications`
> already exists with 4 tasks done.

**Correct behavior:**
> Agent reads `memory-bank/progress.md`, finds `TASK-003` through `TASK-006`
> already marked Done under the notifications feature board. Agent responds:
> *"Notifications is already In Progress â€” TASK-003 through TASK-006 are
> Done. The next open task is TASK-007 (NotificationList component). Run
> `/speckit-implement TASK-007` to continue."*
